article.headline: Kent State 70, Ball State 67
article.story: KENT, Ohio (AP) -- Matt Jakeway scored 16 points and hit two free throws with eight seconds to play to help Kent State beat Ball State 70-67 Saturday night. Kent State (8-2, 2-0 Mid-American Conference) took the lead for good at 63-61 on Bryan Bedford's layup with 2:27 left. Eric Haut and John Edwards, both of whom also finished with 16 points, hit two free throws apiece as the Golden Flashes widened their lead to 67-61 with 53 seconds to play. Ball State (3-6, 0-1 ), which was led by Dennis Trammell's 21 points, got within 67-63 on Matt McCollum's two free throws with 40 seconds left. After DeAndre Haynes split a pair of free throws for Kent State, Terrence Chapman made one free throw to make it 68-64 with 12 seconds to play. Trammell followed Jakeway's final two three throws with a 3-pointer with one second left.
